Okay so this is egotistical but I did want to shout my own work here: "John: Load Save", It's a "retcon" fixit deconstruction, that talks about how fanon assumptions of characters contrast with canon, and what it means to be "canon". It deconstructs the idea that hussie's insert presents  to caliborn during trickster mode, that there are "consequences" for "skipping past" a character's arc. However, instead of reckoning with the consequences of that skip (aka the epilogues, beyond canon), it explores the emotional fallout that comes with actually dealing with the problems that are deemed "character flaws", and how the characters being adults during the game might have changed how acts 5 onward would have played out.
